WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.033 --> 00:00:06.167
WE'VE BUILT OURSELVES A BOAT.

00:00:06.167 --> 00:00:08.501
WE HAVE PROVISIONED IT
FOR AT LEAST A FEW WEEKS AT SEA,

00:00:08.501 --> 00:00:12.267
AND SOON WE'RE ABOUT TO HEAD OUT
INTO THE GREAT BLUE YONDER

00:00:12.267 --> 00:00:13.601
TO TRY AND GET OURSELVES HOME.

00:00:13.601 --> 00:00:16.400
Narrator: AND WHEN ADAM SAYS
THEY'VE PROVISIONED IT

00:00:16.400 --> 00:00:19.501
FOR A FEW WEEKS,
HE'S NOT EXAGGERATING.

00:00:19.501 --> 00:00:21.667
HERE'S WHAT WE'RE TAKING
ON OUR JOURNEY.

00:00:21.667 --> 00:00:23.934
WE GOT ROPE,
WE GOT FISHING LINE,

00:00:23.934 --> 00:00:26.901
WE GOT BAILERS, OARS, DUCT TAPE.

00:00:26.901 --> 00:00:28.367
WE HAVE TARPS.

00:00:28.367 --> 00:00:31.567
WE HAVE WATER BAGS, FOOD BAGS,
AND A FISHING SPEAR.

00:00:31.567 --> 00:00:35.133
IF THAT DOESN'T HELP US MAKE IT,
WE WEREN'T MEANT TO.

00:00:35.133 --> 00:00:37.801
Jamie: I THINK
WE'RE READY TO PUT IT IN, HUH?

00:00:37.801 --> 00:00:39.601
LET'S CARRY IT DOWN.

00:00:39.601 --> 00:00:40.834
ALL RIGHT.

00:00:40.834 --> 00:00:43.267
Jamie: AT THIS POINT,
WE FOUND THAT DUCT TAPE

00:00:43.267 --> 00:00:45.567
IS NOT A PERFECT SOLUTION
FOR ANYTHING.

00:00:45.567 --> 00:00:46.567
[ GRUNTS ]

00:00:46.567 --> 00:00:49.434
BUT WITH SOME CREATIVITY
IN A PINCH,

00:00:49.434 --> 00:00:53.534
IT'S AN ADEQUATE SOLUTION
FOR JUST ABOUT EVERYTHING.

00:00:53.534 --> 00:00:55.434
NOW, WHETHER IT'LL HOLD UP

00:00:55.434 --> 00:00:59.467
TO A BOAT THAT HAS TO GET US
ACROSS THE OCEAN,

00:00:59.467 --> 00:01:00.901
THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY
TO FIND OUT.

00:01:00.901 --> 00:01:02.667
OKAY.

00:01:02.667 --> 00:01:04.100
[ LAUGHS ]

00:01:04.100 --> 00:01:06.067
AIM IT
TOWARDS THE WAVE.

00:01:06.067 --> 00:01:08.067
WHOA!

00:01:08.067 --> 00:01:10.067
Narrator:
AS THE GUYS CLAMBER IN...

00:01:10.067 --> 00:01:11.934
AAH! AAH! WHOO!

00:01:11.934 --> 00:01:13.334
...IT'S WORTH HIGHLIGHTING

00:01:13.334 --> 00:01:16.100
THAT THE ONE THING
THEY DON'T HAVE IS A MAP.

00:01:16.100 --> 00:01:17.467
[ LAUGHS ]

00:01:17.467 --> 00:01:19.100
Jamie: IT'S WORKING!

00:01:19.100 --> 00:01:20.434
OH, YEAH, BABY!

00:01:20.434 --> 00:01:21.901
Narrator: LIKE REAL CASTAWAYS,

00:01:21.901 --> 00:01:25.501
THEY'RE SIMPLY GOING TO PADDLE
UNTIL THEY FIND LAND OR SINK.

00:01:25.501 --> 00:01:27.934
[ LAUGHS ]
PONTOON'S LOOKING GREAT.

00:01:27.934 --> 00:01:30.434
Narrator: BUT WITH
THE BREAKING WAVES APPROACHING,

00:01:30.434 --> 00:01:32.968
SINKING IS
A VERY REAL POSSIBILITY.

00:01:32.968 --> 00:01:35.234
OH, NO!
HERE WE GO!

00:01:35.234 --> 00:01:36.334
WHOA!

00:01:36.334 --> 00:01:38.400
HEY, IT TOOK IT!

00:01:38.400 --> 00:01:39.734
THERE'S
ANOTHER ONE COMING.

00:01:39.734 --> 00:01:41.000
IT'S BIGGER.

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:42.667
UH-OH! DUDE!

00:01:42.667 --> 00:01:44.133
OH [BLEEP]

00:01:44.133 --> 00:01:45.400
HERE WE GO!

00:01:45.400 --> 00:01:47.000
[ SHOUTS ]

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:48.400
[ BOTH LAUGHING ]

00:01:50.567 --> 00:01:52.234
Adam:
THERE'S NO TWO WAYS ABOUT IT.

00:01:52.234 --> 00:01:54.534
THOSE BREAKERS WERE INTENSE.

00:01:54.534 --> 00:01:55.767
WHOA!

00:01:55.767 --> 00:01:57.267
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

00:01:57.267 --> 00:01:59.467
REMEMBER, WE'RE SITTING THERE
IN A CANOE MADE OF DUCT TAPE...

00:01:59.467 --> 00:02:01.033
COME ON!

00:02:01.033 --> 00:02:04.200
...PADDLING TOWARDS WAVES
THAT ARE LIKE 3 OR 4 FEET HIGHER

00:02:04.200 --> 00:02:05.801
THAN THE PROW OF OUR BOAT.

00:02:05.801 --> 00:02:06.901
WHOA!

00:02:06.901 --> 00:02:08.934
YEAH!

00:02:08.934 --> 00:02:11.100
THAT'S WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT!

00:02:11.100 --> 00:02:13.367
IT WAS ABSOLUTELY TERRIFYING,
BUT ONCE WE MADE IT PAST...

00:02:13.367 --> 00:02:16.067
WHOO! [ LAUGHS ]

00:02:16.067 --> 00:02:18.067
...TOTALLY KNEW WE HAD PASSED

00:02:18.067 --> 00:02:20.100
ONE OF THE WORST HURDLES
WE COULD,

00:02:20.100 --> 00:02:21.567
AND THE BOAT WAS GONNA BE OKAY.

00:02:21.567 --> 00:02:23.133
Narrator: ADAM'S RIGHT.

00:02:23.133 --> 00:02:25.167
HAVING SURVIVED THE BREAKERS...

00:02:25.167 --> 00:02:27.234
HOW DOES SHE LOOK LIKE
SHE'S HOLDING UP IN THE WATER?

00:02:27.234 --> 00:02:28.734
...THE MAIN QUESTION NOW...

00:02:28.734 --> 00:02:30.100
LOOKING GREAT.

00:02:30.100 --> 00:02:32.767
...IS WHETHER THE CANOE
WILL HOLD TOGETHER LONG ENOUGH

00:02:32.767 --> 00:02:36.267
FOR THEM TO FIND CIVILIZATION.

00:02:36.267 --> 00:02:38.400
MAN, IT IS HOT OUT HERE!

00:02:38.400 --> 00:02:41.534
Jamie:
GIVEN THAT WE'RE IN THE OCEAN,
AND IT'S ABOUT 90 DEGREES,

00:02:41.534 --> 00:02:43.367
WE'VE GOT BOTH IN SPADES,

00:02:43.367 --> 00:02:46.000
BUT THE ONLY BAILING
I'M HAVING TO DO SO FAR...

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:48.701
ADAM, I'VE GOT
A LITTLE WATER BACK HERE.

00:02:48.701 --> 00:02:50.834
...IS BECAUSE OF WATER THAT'S
BEING SPLASHED INTO THE BOAT

00:02:50.834 --> 00:02:52.367
RATHER THAN ANY SORT OF LEAK.

00:02:52.367 --> 00:02:54.300
ARE YOU SAYING
MY OAR TECHNIQUE SUCKS?

00:02:54.300 --> 00:02:58.934
Narrator:
TWO HOURS IN AND WITH THEIR
ISLAND NOW A DISTANT MEMORY...

00:02:58.934 --> 00:03:01.000
I CAN'T SEE
THE SHORE ANYMORE.

00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:02.467
WE'RE IN OPEN WATER NOW.

00:03:02.467 --> 00:03:05.367
...ADAM AND JAMIE
START RAIDING THEIR PROVISIONS.

00:03:05.367 --> 00:03:07.067
FIRST WATER...

00:03:07.067 --> 00:03:08.300
YOU WANT SOME?

00:03:08.300 --> 00:03:10.567
...AND THEN FOOD.

00:03:10.567 --> 00:03:13.734
THREE HOURS IN,
AND AN IMPROMPTU FISHING STOP...

00:03:13.734 --> 00:03:15.634
THERE! RIGHT THERE!
AAH!

00:03:15.634 --> 00:03:18.234
...IS ALL THAT SLOWED THEM DOWN.

00:03:18.234 --> 00:03:20.000
[ GROANS ]
I THINK YOU MISSED IT.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:22.234
AS THREE HOURS BECOMES FOUR...

00:03:22.234 --> 00:03:26.000
DUDE, I'M GONNA TAKE
A LITTLE BREAK, OKAY?

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:28.267
...AND FOUR BECOMES FIVE...

00:03:28.267 --> 00:03:31.234
LET'S JUST HOPE
WE'RE NOT PADDLING IN CIRCLES.

00:03:31.234 --> 00:03:35.901
...LET'S PUT THIS
MARITIME MASTERPIECE IN CONTEXT.

00:03:35.901 --> 00:03:37.834
ADAM AND JAMIE'S
YESTERDAY'S NEWS...

00:03:37.834 --> 00:03:40.033
I'M KING OF THE WORLD!
WHOA!

00:03:40.033 --> 00:03:42.734
...BROKE APART IN 20 MINUTES.

00:03:42.734 --> 00:03:45.801
THEIR DUCT-TAPE DINGHY WAS
ON THE WATER NOT MUCH LONGER.

00:03:45.801 --> 00:03:48.200
Jamie: TRY NOT TO PUT YOUR FEET
THROUGH THE BOTTOM.

00:03:48.200 --> 00:03:49.968
AND THEIR ALCATRAZ ESCAPE RAFT

00:03:49.968 --> 00:03:52.067
WAS AN ACCIDENT
WAITING TO HAPPEN.

00:03:52.067 --> 00:03:54.267
I HAVE NO IDEA
WHERE WE ARE.

00:03:54.267 --> 00:03:59.067
BUT THEIR DUCT-TAPE CANOE
HAS NOW BEEN IN THE OPEN OCEAN

00:03:59.067 --> 00:04:02.567
FOR OVER HALF A DAY
AND IS STILL GOING STRONG.

00:04:02.567 --> 00:04:04.968
THIS BOAT --
STRONGEST CASE YET

00:04:04.968 --> 00:04:07.367
THAT DUCT TAPE IS
A FRICKIN' MIRACLE MATERIAL.

00:04:07.367 --> 00:04:10.868
YEAH, THERE'S NO UNDERESTIMATING
THE POWER OF DUCT TAPE.

00:04:10.868 --> 00:04:13.534
WITH NEITHER A LEAK NOR A TEAR,

00:04:13.534 --> 00:04:15.467
YOU MIGHT SAY
IT'S BEEN PLAIN SAILING.

00:04:15.467 --> 00:04:17.367
AND WHAT'S MORE...

00:04:17.367 --> 00:04:18.300
DUDE!

00:04:18.300 --> 00:04:20.334
LAND!
-I SEE IT.

00:04:20.334 --> 00:04:21.434
[ LAUGHS ]

00:04:21.434 --> 00:04:24.934
...AT LAST, AFTER CLOSE
TO SEVEN HOURS AT SEA,

00:04:24.934 --> 00:04:27.300
LAND LOOMS LARGE
ON THE HORIZON.

